abstract: JPMorgan Chase warned Thursday that up to 41 percent of its more creditworthy home-equity borrowers would owe more than their homes are worth by the end of 2010, up from 27 percent at the end of 2008.
lead_paragraph: JPMorgan Chase warned Thursday that up to 41 percent of its more creditworthy home-equity borrowers would owe more than their homes are worth by the end of 2010, up from 27 percent at the end of 2008.

headline.main: JPMorgan Warns of Home-Equity Loan Losses
